Koor Falls Most in Two Weeks on Credit Suisse Share Drop

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-09-04T14:31:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-04/koor-industries-falls-most-in-two-weeks-on-credit-suisse-decline.html
Koor Industries Ltd. (KOR)  lost the most
in two weeks week following a drop in Credit Suisse Group AG
shares.  Koor shares slid 3.9 percent, the biggest retreat since
Aug. 21, to 34.01 shekels at the 4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv.
Koor’s controlling shareholder  Discount Investment Corp. (DISI)  lost 5
percent to 31.43 shekels. Credit Suisse fell 5.6 percent, the
biggest decline since Aug. 18, to 21.76 Swiss francs in trading
in Switzerland on Sept. 2.  “The drops are connected to the fall of Credit Suisse
shares,” Noam Pincu, an analyst at Psagot Investment House Ltd.
in Tel Aviv, said by telephone.  Koor holds 26.2 million shares of Switzerland’s second-
largest bank, the company said Aug. 14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
